data.text:
How to use IDBI Silapathar IFSC code in online fund transfer?

IDBI Silapathar IFSC code is an 11 digit code used in online fund transfers. This IFSC code contains 4 Characters that represent IDBI Bank, 5th character is reserved for future use and the last 6 characters represent the Silapathar branch code. IDBI Bank has many branches all over the country and physical cheques cannot be transferred anywhere across the country to transfer funds hence internet banking is preferred. The IFSC code IBKL0001511 is used to identify the IDBI Silapathar participating in online transactions via RTGS, IMPS and NEFT systems.
